edu.csus.plugin.securecodingassistant.compilation

Class NodeVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTVisitor
      • edu.csus.plugin.securecodingassistant.compilation.NodeVisitor

  • public class NodeVisitor
extends ASTVisitor
    A custom ASTVisitor for the Secure Coding Assistant that checks each ASTNode on the AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) to see if there has been a rule violation. This node visitor must be given a list of IRule rules to check for as well as the existing list of the InsecureCodeSegment objects to prevent the creation of duplicate violations.
    Author:
    Ben White
    See Also:
    IRule, SecureCompilationParticipant, InsecureCodeSegment
